South African Corn Advances, Tracking Gains by U.S. Benchmark

-- B y   M k h u l u l i   M a n c o t y w a
-- 
2011-02-28T10:19:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-28/south-african-corn-advances-tracking-gains-by-u-s-benchmark.html
Corn advanced in  South Africa , the
continent’s largest producer of the grain, after prices rose in
the U.S., which competes for African export markets.  White corn for July delivery added 16.80 rand, or 1
percent, to 1,641.80 rand ($235) a metric ton on the  South
African Futures Exchange  in Johannesburg. Meal made from the
grain is the country’s staple food.  Corn futures in  Chicago  jumped 3.7 percent on Feb. 25 and
were 0.4 percent lower today.  Yellow corn for July delivery gained 118 rand, or 0.7
percent, to 1,683 rand a ton. The grain is used mainly as  animal
feed  in  South Africa .  Wheat for May delivery increased 38 rand, or 1.2 percent,
to 3,175 rand a ton.  The gains or losses for the most active contracts of the
following crops today were as follows. All prices are in rand
and the crops are sold in tons:  To contact the reporter on this story:
